class Solution {
public:
    int minPartitions(string n) {
        int max_digit = 0;
        for (char c : n) {
            max_digit = max(max_digit, c - '0');
        }
        return max_digit;
    }
};
```

efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution iterates through the string once to find the maximum digit, which represents the minimum number of deci-binary numbers needed to sum up to the given number. This approach is efficient because it only requires a single pass through the string and uses a constant amount of space.

